<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06183143 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06183143 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Mallon  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  GOLF; WOMEN; CHAMPIONSHIP; RESULT; MARYLAND  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Meg Mallon's 10-foot birdie putt on No. 18 broke a three-way tie for the leadSunday, giving her the LPGA Championship in Bethesda, Md.;    Mallon, PatBradley and Ayako Okamoto were tied at 9 under par going into the final hole,a 379-yard par 4. After each hit the fairway in good shape, Mallon knocked herapproach within striking distance and dropped in the putt after Bradley andOkamoto parred the hole.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MALLON SINKS BIRDIE PUTT ON NO. 18 FOR LPGATITLEBRADLEY, OKAMOTO SETTLE FOR 2ND-PLACE TIE  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Golf Roundup  </MEMO><TEXT>     It was only the second tournament victory for Mallon, whose first win alsocame this year. In four previous years on the LPGA Tour, she had not finishedhigher than third in any event or better than 27th on the money list.;    &quot;Ifelt like I wasn't getting much respect this week,&quot; said Mallon, who shot afinal-round 67 for a 10-under 274. &quot;I shot a 68 the first day and maybe twopeople talked to me. The same thing the next day. But that was good, becauseit kept things low-key.&quot;;    In winning $150,000, Mallon scored her biggestpayday, and Okamoto and Bradley tied for second. Defending champ Beth Danielwas fourth at 278, with Barb Bunkowsky and Deb Richard at 279.;  COUPLES WINS:Fred Couples got the break he needed when Peter Persons hit into the water onNos. 11 and 12, and Couples won by three strokes in the $1 million St. JudeClassic in Memphis, Tenn.;    Couples had birdies at Nos. 12 and 14 to pullaway. He finished at 15-under 269.;    Rick Fehr, the first-round leader,closed with a 67 to take second. Jay Haas and David Canipe shot 65s for 273totals in a tie for third.;  ETC.: Jim Colbert's final-round 68 allowed him tooutduel co-leader Al Geiberger and capture his first PGA Senior Tour victory,a three-stroke triumph in a $450,000 event in Belton, Mo. Colbert had a54-hole total of 9-under-par 201.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910701  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  332  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday July 1, 199100183143,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>